The paper deals with the problem of compressing Euclidean metrics, which is a fundamental problem in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The main focus is on the $\ell_2$ and $\ell_1$ norms, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the Johnson-Lindenstrauss dimensionality reduction theorem, which is a well-known result in theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
